2. cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper discusses the use of a Transformer-based model for modeling the relationship between different modalities, which is a common technique in natural language processing.
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper describes a pre-training strategy for enhancing the quality of the model, which is a key aspect of machine learning.
4. cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The paper evaluates the pre-trained model on image retrieval and text retrieval tasks, which are core topics in information retrieval.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper deals with the joint embedding of images and text, which is a core topic in multimedia research.
